6. Phase 5: Bilingual runtime behavior (depends on 2, supports 3-5)
1. Implement ES/EN toggle on both pages via translation keys and shared state.
2. Keep html lang attribute synchronized with selected language.
3. Translate ARIA and validation feedback strings consistently.
7. Phase 6: Quality hardening (depends on 3-6)
1. Accessibility: keyboard-only flow, visible focus states, contrast checks, logical tab order, live-region announcements.
2. GEO and E-E-A-T: answer-first section intros, clear entity facts, trust signals via consistent identity/contact/program scope.
3. Architectural guardrails to avoid:
1. Non-crawlable JS-only critical content
2. Div-only layouts replacing semantic tags
3. Heavy custom CSS overriding Tailwind utility-first approach
8. Phase 7: Verification and readiness (depends on all)
1. Content fidelity check against context.html.
2. Validation matrix for each field and all dependent select combinations.
3. Responsive checks on mobile/tablet/desktop.
4. Schema validation via Rich Results.
5. Accessibility checks via keyboard + Lighthouse.
6. Performance validation on https://brasaland.com with PageSpeed target >=80 (ideal >90).

